1
00:01:57,959 --> 00:01:58,799
WHERE GOT GHOST?

2
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:07,799
GHOST ON THE ROADSIDE

3
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,000
YUNNAN SHANTANG

4
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:24,240
There are two children outside,
looking at us and wanting to come in.

5
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:27,000
Who are their parents?

6
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:32,280
Never mind.
You can't see them anyway.

7
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:36,680
I think they're the children
from your family.

8
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,240
I don't think so, Master.

9
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:44,879
Did anyone have an abortion
or miscarriage years ago?

10
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,360
Never mind.

11
00:03:46,479 --> 00:03:49,919
These children will then follow
the unlucky ones.

12
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,479
Master, are they neighboring kids
who've lost their way home?

13
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:58,240
Will your grandchildren
also go to the wrong doors?

14
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,280
No.

15
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:04,680
Baby spirits can be terrifying.

16
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:07,800
If they're not dealt with properly,

17
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:13,000
these baby spirits
will haunt their parents for life.

18
00:04:13,919 --> 00:04:16,560
-What are we to do then, Master?
-Simple.

19
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,600
Perform a ritual to send them away.

20
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:26,920
Do it then, Master.
Let them reincarnate.

21
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,879
-Okay, $1,000 each.
-What, $1,000?

22
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:32,560
Can it be cheaper?

23
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:35,839
If you're tight on cash,
just do the ritual for one,

24
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:40,879
and the other will stay here
to follow the unlucky ones.

25
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:44,319
Okay, then.

26
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:48,240
-So be it, $2,000.
-Okay.

27
00:04:48,439 --> 00:04:52,600
What toys do you want to burn for them?

28
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,360
Burn toys for them?

29
00:04:54,639 --> 00:04:56,639
This is crucial.

30
00:04:57,079 --> 00:04:58,680
-Show them the catalogue.
-Right away.

31
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:01,600
We're having a promotion.

32
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,680
You'll be given special discount
if you order today.

33
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:08,519
Look at this Transformer.
It's the children's favorite.

34
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:10,079
-Very popular.
-Is it?

35
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:13,519
There are also DS Lite, Ben 10...

36
00:05:13,639 --> 00:05:15,160
PSP is the best.

37
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,279
There's more...

38
00:05:19,079 --> 00:05:20,000
Yours.

39
00:05:21,319 --> 00:05:22,160
Yours.

40
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:23,879
Chief?

41
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,839
Too little?

42
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:25,959
No.

43
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:30,600
If we continue with this act, will we
offend the spirits and get retribution?

44
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:34,160
He's right. I feel uncomfortable,
making money like this.

45
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,680
I get goosebumps every time.

46
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:38,079
There's nothing to be afraid of.

47
00:05:38,199 --> 00:05:41,600
Let me tell you,
there are no ghosts in this world.

48
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:44,480
They exist only to the guilt-stricken
and weak-hearted,

49
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,439
who'll pay us to perform the ritual.

50
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,720
Aren't we still cheating them
out of money?

51
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:51,639
We're executing heaven's will.

52
00:05:51,759 --> 00:05:57,519
These people are willing to pay us
to help them feel better.

53
00:05:57,639 --> 00:06:00,040
What's wrong with that?

54
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:04,879
Chief, what you just said
makes me feel much better now.

55
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:10,240
Okay. Go buy some supper
and some fruits too.

56
00:06:10,399 --> 00:06:14,120
I've been having problems of late.
Must be constipation.

57
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:47,839
Whenever I pass by this place,
it gives me the crisps.

58
00:06:47,959 --> 00:06:49,000
Crisps?

59
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,360
I mean "creeps."

60
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:53,800
Singaporeans can never speak
proper Mandarin. All because of you...

61
00:06:55,199 --> 00:06:56,240
Oh, no!

62
00:06:56,959 --> 00:06:59,360
-What's the matter?
-I forgot to buy fruits!

63
00:06:59,439 --> 00:07:01,720
I'm not going to go alone
to buy them.

64
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,079
I'm fat and tired.

65
00:07:03,279 --> 00:07:04,480
Let's go together then.

66
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:08,319
What's the difference? It's equally far,
and I'll still be fat and tired.

67
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:12,480
What shall we do then?
Expect a scolding from the Chief?

68
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:16,600
I have an idea.
Are you with me?

69
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,319
You want to give the Chief these oranges?

70
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:33,079
Chief said there were no ghosts
in this world.

71
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:35,399
If you don't take them,
the foreign workers will,

72
00:07:35,519 --> 00:07:37,120
and they're fine after eating them.

73
00:07:37,199 --> 00:07:38,079
Are you sure?

74
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:40,600
Have you heard of foreign workers
dying after eating oranges?

75
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,720
-No.
-Then it's okay.

76
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:46,079
You're right.
Anyway, it's for the Chief.

77
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:48,079
I'll never touch them.

78
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:53,800
I'm so sorry, Mr. Spirit.
Our Chief wants to eat these fruits.

79
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,439
Please look for him
if you spirits are unhappy.

80
00:07:56,839 --> 00:07:59,639
His name is "Li Ah Cai."

81
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,879
He's not afraid of you spirits,

82
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,199
but we respect you very much.

83
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,600
Sorry.

84
00:08:05,839 --> 00:08:07,399
I respect you too.

85
00:08:07,519 --> 00:08:08,519
Get the oranges.

86
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:27,000
May I ask, where did you get this orange?

87
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,160
It's tasteless.

88
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,279
It's inedible.

89
00:08:33,399 --> 00:08:36,000
How dare you give me such rubbish?

90
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:40,360
It's sugar-free.

91
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,879
Yes. You'll get diabetes
from eating too much sweet stuff.

92
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
Go to hell!

93
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:49,559
If I get diabetes,
I'll drown you with my urine.

94
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,799
Almost forgot.

95
00:09:15,039 --> 00:09:16,000
Prosperity!

96
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,200
Goal!

97
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,320
I worship to the God of Ball.
Are you insane?

98
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,840
Are you insane?

99
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,519
God of Ball?

100
00:09:26,039 --> 00:09:27,679
I meant the God of Football,

101
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:29,080
who can help me win.

102
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:32,200
You should pray hard not to go insane.

103
00:09:32,519 --> 00:09:33,399
Nuts!

104
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:43,559
Chief, there's a god in everything.

105
00:09:43,679 --> 00:09:46,960
Worship them,
and you'll be blessed and prosperous.

106
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:51,919
Hello?

107
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,639
Congratulations to you, sir.

108
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,559
You've won a prize
in our company's lucky draw.

109
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:58,360
Two first-class round-trip tickets
to America.

110
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:00,279
Please come collect your prize
from our company.

111
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:01,480
Go to hell!

112
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:04,799
You think you can fool me
with these old tricks? Idiots!

113
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:08,200
Can you believe it? They're still trying
to trick people with such calls.

114
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,840
Can't they be more creative?

115
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,360
Full of shit.

116
00:10:12,919 --> 00:10:14,919
Chief, look at it from another angle.

117
00:10:15,039 --> 00:10:17,320
If she makes 10,000 calls,

118
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,879
all she needs
is ten people to buy into the idea,

119
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,519
and they'll be rich.

120
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:26,000
Chief, the same goes
with our everyday lottery system.

121
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:28,919
Out of 10,000 combinations,
there are only 23 possible winners.

122
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,320
You're right.

123
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:43,440
If a person bets from 0000 to 9999,
they'll win 23 combinations for sure.

124
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:52,879
We're going to win big!

125
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,480
What is it, Chief?

126
00:10:56,919 --> 00:10:58,480
From tomorrow,

127
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:01,039
we'll make 10,000 phone calls,

128
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:05,000
from 0000 to 9999,

129
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:07,960
giving each of them
a combination of numbers.

130
00:11:08,159 --> 00:11:10,759
There will surely be 23 winners.

131
00:11:10,879 --> 00:11:14,360
From the smallest to the biggest prize,
we will win them all!

132
00:11:15,919 --> 00:11:20,360
Then we'll get a 20% commission fee
from every winner.

133
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,960
That's a brilliant idea, Chief!

134
00:11:24,399 --> 00:11:28,519
What if they don't buy into our idea
or even deny having won?

135
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:30,080
How do we get a commission then?

136
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:34,000
We'll tell them it's lucky money
from the God of Wealth.

137
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,879
Then they'll pay up accordingly.

138
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,200
Is there a God of Wealth?

139
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:43,399
Yes, I'm the God of Wealth!

140
00:11:44,679 --> 00:11:48,080
-You're a God, Chief!
-We're with a deity!

141
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:55,639
Where can we find 10,000 phone numbers
and addresses?

142
00:11:56,039 --> 00:12:02,720
There's something used to wrap
steamed rice roll and kanchan puti.

143
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:06,960
I'll use it to "win."

144
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,480
You do A to J, and you do K to T.

145
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:17,600
Who will make the calls from U to Z?

146
00:12:18,039 --> 00:12:19,080
Who do you think?

147
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,960
Congratulations!

148
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:26,559
We're calling on behalf
of the God of Wealth. Listen carefully.

149
00:12:26,639 --> 00:12:30,960
Your lucky combination is 1045...

150
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,519
1033...

151
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:37,159
Make the purchase with these numbers.
If you win...

152
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:41,440
Please donate
20% of the winnings to our foundation.

153
00:12:41,519 --> 00:12:45,440
The donation will be used to build
a temple for the God of Wealth,

154
00:12:45,559 --> 00:12:47,360
not for our personal use.

155
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,120
Thank you.
We wish you the best of luck.

156
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,120
Win big!

157
00:12:59,159 --> 00:13:02,639
The first prize of the week goes to...

158
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:06,360
1045.

159
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,200
I've won again!

160
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:12,080
I made the calls for the top three prizes.
Take a look.

161
00:13:12,159 --> 00:13:13,039
Get lost!

162
00:13:13,159 --> 00:13:14,399
What's the celebration for?

163
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:20,559
Chief, the calls for the top three prizes
were all made by me. I'm so lucky!

164
00:13:20,919 --> 00:13:22,360
It's only the top three prizes.

165
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:25,080
I made the calls
for the rest of the combinations.

166
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,919
A total of 20 prizes.

167
00:13:27,039 --> 00:13:28,919
I'm luckier than you.

168
00:13:29,039 --> 00:13:30,519
So great, huh?

169
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,960
-You both made all the winning calls?
-Yes.

170
00:13:33,039 --> 00:13:34,399
Did you win any prize?

171
00:13:35,399 --> 00:13:36,440
No.

172
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:38,480
What's there to celebrate?

173
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:44,639
Chief, we may not be the winners,
but we made those calls.

174
00:13:44,759 --> 00:13:46,080
It still feels amazing.

175
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:49,919
Although I didn't win for a long time,
this feels good too.

176
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,279
Morons. I look at it differently.

177
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:55,840
I came up with this system,

178
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,240
so I knew all along

179
00:13:57,399 --> 00:14:01,120
that those 23 combinations
would be my winning combinations.

180
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:03,080
I'm the ultimate winner!

181
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:08,960
Take down the addresses
and collect our commissions quickly.

182
00:14:19,679 --> 00:14:22,440
I'm such a genius.

183
00:14:39,159 --> 00:14:41,159
Congratulations
on winning the third prize.

184
00:14:41,399 --> 00:14:44,840
I told you,
this money is from the God of Wealth.

185
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:49,879
You'll need to donate
20% of the prize money to our foundation.

186
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,879
I'll send you the God of Wealth's
account number via SMS.

187
00:14:53,279 --> 00:14:54,919
Thank you.

188
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,159
Win big!

189
00:14:56,279 --> 00:15:01,399
Let me tell you,
Lady Luck will be on your side very often!

190
00:15:02,039 --> 00:15:03,399
Win big!

191
00:15:04,799 --> 00:15:06,559
This is not right!

192
00:15:06,639 --> 00:15:09,399
You didn't bet on
the second-prize combination?

193
00:15:09,559 --> 00:15:11,759
This is the God of Wealth's prize money.

194
00:15:11,879 --> 00:15:14,799
You can lie to us,
but not to the God of Wealth.

195
00:15:15,559 --> 00:15:18,200
Also... Hello? Hello?

196
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:21,240
He hung up on me.
What shall we do?

197
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:24,000
Have you been in the army before?

198
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:26,360
Your size is out of standard anyway.

199
00:15:26,639 --> 00:15:29,840
They have something called
a "contingency plan."

200
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:31,519
So does our business.

201
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,519
Where does this guy live?

202
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:39,080
She's the one refusing
to pay us commission!

203
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,080
No worries, I'll call her.

204
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,960
Are you Chen Xiaohua?

205
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,360
Yes, who's this?

206
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:52,519
Congratulation on winning the lottery.
Our God of Wealth never fails to deliver.

207
00:15:52,639 --> 00:15:54,960
Please donate money
to help us build a temple.

208
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:57,559
I've told you,
I didn't bet on the combination.

209
00:15:57,679 --> 00:15:59,440
How could I win if I didn't place the bet?

210
00:15:59,559 --> 00:16:01,840
This is the God of Wealth's money.

211
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:05,200
If you've placed the bet,
you can lie to us, but not to a deity.

212
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,720
I've told you so many times,

213
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,039
how could I win if I didn't place the bet?

214
00:16:09,519 --> 00:16:11,720
-Really?
-Really.

215
00:16:11,799 --> 00:16:13,320
No worries.

216
00:16:13,399 --> 00:16:18,799
Don't blame me
for any misfortune in the future.

217
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:21,360
So be it. Bye

218
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,080
-Okay?
-Okay

219
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,879
-Remember the target.
-Her head, right?

220
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,240
No, just to scare her.

221
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,279
Missed her head.

222
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:46,240
Your aim must have been lousy
during your army days.

223
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:50,559
It's not easy to miss on purpose.
She'll transfer the funds to us tomorrow.

224
00:16:51,919 --> 00:16:57,720
But this won't be feasible
when we have more customers.

225
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:00,080
We'll seek help from professionals.

226
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,200
Professionals?

227
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,320
Loan sharks.

228
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,839
I see.

229
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,960
I don't owe you any money.

230
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:12,240
I'm not a loan shark. The God of Wealth
gave you your lucky money.

231
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:14,720
-Why didn't you make a donation?
-Donation!

232
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,599
Donation! Donation!

233
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:24,759
-I didn't place the bet.
-Are you certain?

234
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:28,960
You sure? You sure?

235
00:17:33,359 --> 00:17:35,079
TRANSFER

236
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:40,839
I can't stop smiling.

237
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:44,160
Chief, this is easy money.

238
00:17:44,279 --> 00:17:46,160
Our business will be great!

239
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:49,079
Chief, your idea is brilliant.

240
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,880
We need to copyright it.
If not, there will be copy dogs.

241
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,480
It's "copycat," not "copy dog"!

242
00:17:56,799 --> 00:18:01,000
You're right. I'll need more manpower.

243
00:18:01,759 --> 00:18:06,960
Recruit 100 students
with sweet voices to make the calls.

244
00:18:14,319 --> 00:18:17,960
I'll run the business like an enterprise,

245
00:18:18,039 --> 00:18:19,440
have my company listed.

246
00:18:19,559 --> 00:18:21,519
Then I'll be filthy rich!

247
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:24,960
I'm a genius, indeed!

248
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:31,880
GOD OF WEALTH ENTERPRISE

249
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:43,319
Hello. I'm a representative
of the God of Wealth Enterprise.

250
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,480
Good fortune to you.

251
00:18:47,559 --> 00:18:49,759
Your lucky combination is 2305.

252
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:50,880
...6111.

253
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:54,799
However, if you win a prize...

254
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:58,480
Please donate 20% of your prize money
to us to build temples.

255
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,559
-Thank you.
-May you prosper!

256
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:03,839
Wow!

257
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:06,599
What's up?

258
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,400
If we continue making money like this,
We can afford the largest plasma TV

259
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:13,519
for next year's World Cup Live!

260
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:15,799
Are you okay?

261
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:19,039
If this continues,
we won't be watching TV,

262
00:19:19,279 --> 00:19:21,279
but flying first class
to South Africa

263
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,119
to watch the match live!

264
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,359
You're right.

265
00:19:24,759 --> 00:19:29,079
From 0000 to 9999,
there are 10,000 combinations.

266
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:32,279
Place a bet on one combination,
and you'll stand a chance to win a prize.

267
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,119
This is called "Four-Digit Lottery"
or "4D."

268
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:39,200
This lottery has been in Singapore
for decades.

269
00:19:39,319 --> 00:19:40,839
It's a brilliant idea,

270
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:44,200
because anyone who bets
will feel a strong sense of victory.

271
00:19:44,319 --> 00:19:45,839
It's very popular among citizens,

272
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,720
and also very good business
for the organization.

273
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:52,240
That's why even our government
is actively involved.

274
00:19:52,839 --> 00:19:54,240
If you're interested,

275
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:57,680
I can make arrangements
for you to meet our officials.

276
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,839
Get back to me quickly.

277
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,200
Time for lunch, Chief.

278
00:20:02,079 --> 00:20:04,359
Chief, the Taiwanese are also interested?

279
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,920
Not only Taiwan!

280
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:12,960
My targets also include Hong Kong, Korea,
Japan, the US, England, Australia, Africa,

281
00:20:13,039 --> 00:20:16,920
and all the countries in the world!
Everyone will buy my lottery,

282
00:20:19,039 --> 00:20:21,799
including Westerners!

283
00:20:24,279 --> 00:20:26,599
I'm a genius, indeed!

284
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:32,480
Congratulations. I'm here
to bring you good fortune.

285
00:20:32,599 --> 00:20:33,920
Please take down this combination,

286
00:20:34,039 --> 00:20:35,960
6-6-6-6.

287
00:20:36,039 --> 00:20:38,400
Damn it! Someone is using our idea,

288
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:40,799
and they're telling me
to place a bet on 6666!

289
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:41,759
Really?

290
00:20:42,359 --> 00:20:44,480
-Hello?
-If you win,

291
00:20:44,599 --> 00:20:47,759
please donate 18% of the prize money
to our charity.

292
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,119
Go to hell!

293
00:20:49,519 --> 00:20:52,480
They're even cutting commissions
to compete with us!

294
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:57,039
Yes, I told you to get the idea
copyrighted. Did you do it?

295
00:20:57,119 --> 00:20:59,400
I did. They said you need
to wait five years.

296
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:02,000
Five years?
I'll starve to death!

297
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,960
Chief, want to place the bet on 6666?

298
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:06,799
My foot!

299
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,599
What if it wins the lottery?

300
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:12,079
It could be one
of the 23 winning combinations.

301
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,720
I hate both of you!

302
00:21:16,119 --> 00:21:18,200
-Bet a little then.
-How much?

303
00:21:18,279 --> 00:21:20,079
$200!

304
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:24,119
Get going, before it's too late!

305
00:21:26,279 --> 00:21:29,400
-Bet a little then?
-$200?

306
00:21:36,559 --> 00:21:38,920
...8-9-0-1.

307
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:41,680
The numbers are

308
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,599
1-1-5-5.

309
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:47,119
-Did the numbers win?
-Nope.

310
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:49,440
I knew it.
That guy cannot be trusted.

311
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,039
The third-prize combination is

312
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:56,279
6-6-6-7.

313
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:59,920
Didn't I tell you? I knew it all along.
It's utter rubbish.

314
00:22:00,559 --> 00:22:02,200
The second-prize combination is

315
00:22:02,319 --> 00:22:06,000
6-6-6-6.

316
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,240
Hurray!

317
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:09,359
It's a windfall!

318
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:11,799
The first-prize combination is

319
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:16,279
6-6-6-6.

320
00:22:19,119 --> 00:22:22,920
It's spot on!
This guy is a deity!

321
00:22:23,039 --> 00:22:26,039
-He's so spot on with his prediction!
-What did you say is a deity?

322
00:22:26,119 --> 00:22:29,400
I meant the table is dirty.

323
00:22:29,799 --> 00:22:30,680
Dirty?

324
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:34,559
You're such an idiot!
Our Chief is the most formidable.

325
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,039
Cheers to our Chief!

326
00:22:36,519 --> 00:22:37,440
Cheers!

327
00:22:41,039 --> 00:22:43,000
-Hello?
-Congratulations.

328
00:22:43,119 --> 00:22:45,240
You've won the first and second prizes.

329
00:22:45,359 --> 00:22:46,880
I told you.

330
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:49,359
Please make your donation soon.

331
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:52,359
This is my idea.

332
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:55,599
You've stolen my idea,
and you expect a commission from me?

333
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:58,480
You're a moron!
Come and collect the money if you dare.

334
00:22:58,599 --> 00:23:01,359
You haven't even paid me royalties.

335
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,680
You're such a loser!

336
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:06,079
Hope you get H1N1!

337
00:23:06,759 --> 00:23:07,960
What's wrong?

338
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,640
He wants an 18% commission?

339
00:23:09,759 --> 00:23:12,119
Who cares? Let's toast!

340
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:14,759
You guys deserve a treat.

341
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:17,319
Tonight, you can order
whatever you want. Go ahead!

342
00:23:18,559 --> 00:23:19,599
Let's drink!

343
00:23:21,799 --> 00:23:23,119
Let's drink!

344
00:23:29,759 --> 00:23:32,920
$800,000 is so heavy!

345
00:23:33,119 --> 00:23:35,000
-Let me help you, Chief.
-No need.

346
00:23:35,079 --> 00:23:37,480
-I can lend you a hand.
-That won't be necessary.

347
00:23:37,559 --> 00:23:39,440
We need to be discreet.
Hurry up.

348
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:43,359
You're old and skinny.
The money is safer with me.

349
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,119
Not required!

350
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:48,319
You have arthritis, Chief.
The weight is bad for your bones.

351
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:50,160
I said not required.

352
00:23:50,319 --> 00:23:53,160
-I'm big. I can protect the money.
-Not required!

353
00:23:53,279 --> 00:23:55,400
Chief...

354
00:23:55,839 --> 00:23:56,680
Say no more.

355
00:23:56,799 --> 00:23:58,039
Let me carry it for a while.

356
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:00,039
I've never felt the weight of $800,000!

357
00:24:00,119 --> 00:24:01,519
No!

358
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,519
Chief, let me have it for a while.

359
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:06,160
I'm willing to break my leg for it.

360
00:24:06,279 --> 00:24:07,640
Over my dead body!

361
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:10,480
I beg of you. Let's play
rock-paper-scissors to decide.

362
00:24:10,599 --> 00:24:12,359
Say no more!

363
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:24,680
-What's up?
-Who are you looking for?

364
00:24:25,519 --> 00:24:29,039
You won the prize.
Why didn't you make the donation?

365
00:24:30,759 --> 00:24:32,960
So you're that H1N1 loser!

366
00:24:33,079 --> 00:24:36,599
You stole my idea!
How dare you demand a commission from me?

367
00:24:36,839 --> 00:24:40,839
Your winning combination was given
by the Granny of Wealth behind me.

368
00:24:41,759 --> 00:24:45,039
The prize-money donation
will be given to her.

369
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,480
Granny?

370
00:24:46,759 --> 00:24:48,240
What Granny?

371
00:24:50,799 --> 00:24:54,400
Look at him, copying all our ideas!

372
00:24:55,359 --> 00:24:56,759
Don't you have better tricks?

373
00:24:56,839 --> 00:24:58,839
Your brain must be rusty.

374
00:25:00,079 --> 00:25:04,240
She's right behind me.
Didn't you see her?

375
00:25:06,079 --> 00:25:08,119
Yes!

376
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:11,839
-And I can even see Grandpa too!
-Right!

377
00:25:13,119 --> 00:25:15,720
Grandpa is cooking it salty

378
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:18,079
Granny wants it less salty

379
00:25:18,559 --> 00:25:22,359
Granny brought you such fortune,
you ungrateful bastards!

380
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:24,400
You'll be knocked down by a car.

381
00:25:29,839 --> 00:25:32,119
Loser, trying to frighten me?

382
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:35,519
I'm so scared, my limbs are trembling.
I'm peeing in my pants.

383
00:25:36,119 --> 00:25:40,200
I'll cross the road now.
Let's see if cars knock me down.

384
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:45,799
Come on, run me over!

385
00:25:50,279 --> 00:25:54,000
-Come back, Chief!
-Run me over!

386
00:25:57,519 --> 00:25:58,759
It's dangerous!

387
00:26:00,079 --> 00:26:02,119
Did you see that?
I'm perfectly okay!

388
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:05,519
-Come back, Chief!
-Get the cars to knock me down!

389
00:26:06,119 --> 00:26:07,519
I'm invincible!

390
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:11,359
Look up! Run for your life!

391
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,880
Chief!

392
00:26:50,559 --> 00:26:55,440
Next time, don't eat my oranges.

393
00:26:59,319 --> 00:27:00,720
Ghost!

394
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:08,119
I'm so sorry, Mr. Spirit.
Our Chief wants to eat these fruits.

395
00:27:08,200 --> 00:27:10,799
Please look for him
if you spirits are unhappy.

396
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,880
His name is "Li Ah Cai."

397
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,680
He's not afraid of you spirits,

398
00:27:16,759 --> 00:27:18,799
but we respect you very much.

399
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:20,400
Sorry.

400
00:27:20,519 --> 00:27:21,880
I respect you too.

401
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:22,920
Get the oranges.

402
00:27:28,839 --> 00:27:30,480
It's inedible.

403
00:27:30,559 --> 00:27:32,880
How dare you give me such rubbish?

404
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,440
DISASTERS IN LIFE

405
00:28:01,839 --> 00:28:04,960
START WITH IGNORING DETAILS.

406
00:28:07,039 --> 00:28:10,039
THERE ARE GHOSTS IN THE WOODS

407
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:20,640
Faster!

408
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,240
Yes, Master Sergeant!

409
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:50,480
Don't take this lightly!

410
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:52,480
Don't take shortcuts!

411
00:28:53,279 --> 00:28:54,720
Don't be lazy!

412
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,400
Don't be a smartass!

413
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,759
Yes, Warrant Officer.

414
00:29:24,039 --> 00:29:25,319
No, Warrant Officer.

415
00:29:44,799 --> 00:29:47,279
Put on your helmet on.
Move out.

416
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:58,279
Sir, can we be the last detail?

417
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:01,440
Can, come back next Sunday.

418
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:03,880
Report to the Master Sergeant.

419
00:30:13,599 --> 00:30:15,160
Report to the Master Sergeant.

420
00:30:21,559 --> 00:30:25,359
I heard that this forest is cursed.

421
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:27,359
-So?
-Many Japanese soldiers died here.

422
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:29,279
-What are you afraid of?
-Ghosts.

423
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:31,440
You look like a ghost yourself,
and you're scared?

424
00:30:33,119 --> 00:30:36,039
Buddy, slow down.
I have something to tell you.

425
00:30:36,119 --> 00:30:36,960
What is it?

426
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:40,759
My reasons for trying
to take off are all valid!

427
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:41,839
What are you trying to say?

428
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,640
I've seen five masters.

429
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,240
They all told me the same thing,

430
00:30:45,359 --> 00:30:47,200
that I'm cursed
with a "blood encounter" this year.

431
00:30:47,319 --> 00:30:50,880
"Blood encounter" curse?
Don't get me into trouble. I'm your buddy.

432
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,160
-How's your luck been this year?
-Extremely good, man.

433
00:30:53,279 --> 00:30:54,799
That'll do. You can save me.

434
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,720
But what if I'm cursed
by your bad luck instead?

435
00:30:56,799 --> 00:30:57,759
No.

436
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:00,279
No? I must complain
to the Ministry of Defense.

437
00:31:00,359 --> 00:31:02,519
They'll need to consult my masters

438
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,160
before assigning me
a buddy from now on.

439
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:05,680
Right.

440
00:31:05,839 --> 00:31:08,119
Stop. Don't move.

441
00:31:09,759 --> 00:31:12,400
See? I've lifted
your "blood encounter" curse for you!

442
00:31:12,519 --> 00:31:14,480
-Thank you.
-Don't move.

443
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:17,839
Blood encounter.

444
00:31:20,319 --> 00:31:21,440
Stop!

445
00:31:22,119 --> 00:31:25,319
B-L-O-O-D E-N-C-O-U-N-T-E-R!

446
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:26,839
Are you trying to get back to me?

447
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:28,920
These mosquitoes are formidable.

448
00:31:29,039 --> 00:31:32,000
Just can't seem to hit any of them!

449
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:34,119
Buddy!

450
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,880
I think we're lost.

451
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,640
Says who? See?
We came this way, and we're here!

452
00:31:39,759 --> 00:31:42,480
No, we came that way, and we're here!

453
00:31:42,599 --> 00:31:44,759
No, we're there.

454
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:46,880
Don't argue with me.
We're at this point.

455
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:50,160
-Take that thing out.
-That "thing" is called a compass.

456
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:53,759
See?

457
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:58,960
I think it's broken.

458
00:31:59,039 --> 00:32:00,839
The compass points to this direction.

459
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:03,079
When you turn around,

460
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:06,240
it still points to the same direction.

461
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:08,240
If you turn back,

462
00:32:08,319 --> 00:32:09,880
it still points to the same direction.

463
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,839
It's definitely broken!

464
00:32:12,119 --> 00:32:13,599
Don't you know?

465
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,920
This is how a compass works.

466
00:32:16,039 --> 00:32:18,240
It always point in the same direction.

467
00:32:18,319 --> 00:32:21,079
It's always pointing to "Nan,"
meaning South.

468
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:22,200
How do you know?

469
00:32:22,279 --> 00:32:23,319
-Do you see an "N" on it?
-Yes.

470
00:32:26,279 --> 00:32:27,799
What about the "S"?

471
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:31,400
"S" is "See," meaning West.

472
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,920
What about the "W"?

473
00:32:34,039 --> 00:32:35,960
"W" stands for...

474
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:39,000
There are women over there.
It's dangerous.

475
00:32:39,119 --> 00:32:40,599
Rubbish!

476
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:42,720
So "E" stands for "Elephant"?

477
00:32:42,799 --> 00:32:45,279
Don't fool me.
You think I don't know topography?

478
00:32:45,599 --> 00:32:48,720
In fact, I really know nothing
about it! I used to be a military driver.

479
00:32:48,799 --> 00:32:53,119
There's always someone
to tell me directions.

480
00:32:53,359 --> 00:32:54,960
I know nothing about topography really.

481
00:32:55,559 --> 00:32:57,079
I used to be in the military police.

482
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:59,759
I arrested people every day,

483
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,480
so I don't know topography either.

484
00:33:01,559 --> 00:33:03,839
I always lazed around in my army days.

485
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:06,160
I used to be second sergeant.
Then I got demoted to third sergeant.

486
00:33:06,319 --> 00:33:07,480
Can you be worse than me?

487
00:33:07,599 --> 00:33:11,160
I went from first sergeant to corporal,
then back to third sergeant.

488
00:33:11,279 --> 00:33:15,200
I was locked in the detention barracks
three times!

489
00:33:16,079 --> 00:33:17,240
Three times?

490
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:19,640
No big deal.
My record was five times.

491
00:33:19,759 --> 00:33:23,400
Listen carefully.
I was locked for 40 days every time.

492
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:25,200
You win!

493
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:26,920
Let's take a look.

494
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:31,680
If we follow the instructions,
we'll be here forever.

495
00:33:31,799 --> 00:33:33,000
What shall we do then?

496
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:35,720
Do you dare?

497
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,279
-What are you talking about?
-Shortcut.

498
00:33:41,759 --> 00:33:43,440
Buddy!

499
00:33:43,559 --> 00:33:45,000
Why do we need to prowl like this?

500
00:33:45,119 --> 00:33:46,279
We're taking a shortcut.

501
00:33:46,359 --> 00:33:49,400
This tactical movement
will keep us from officers' view.

502
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,920
-This is the shortcut?
-Yes.

503
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:08,000
This is the Pan Island Expressway.

504
00:34:08,079 --> 00:34:11,840
Idiot, we'll take a cab
from here straight to the end point.

505
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:13,039
Go to hell!

506
00:34:19,119 --> 00:34:22,239
Pass me the map and follow me closely.

507
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:24,199
Learn from me, kiddo.

508
00:34:24,519 --> 00:34:25,760
Let's see what you can do.

509
00:34:44,519 --> 00:34:47,519
Why is there a tombstone
in the military training area?

510
00:34:49,559 --> 00:34:50,440
Let's go.

511
00:34:50,519 --> 00:34:52,119
Is there a lucky number on it?

512
00:34:52,199 --> 00:34:54,960
-Cut the crap. Let's go.
-She is so pretty.

513
00:34:55,039 --> 00:34:57,920
-Don't say "pretty."
-Okay, she's ugly.

514
00:35:00,639 --> 00:35:02,719
Stop uttering rubbish! Let's go!

515
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:07,519
What's wrong with saying
"ugly" or "pretty"?

516
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:14,039
LU-YIN

