-It can be dangerous!

791
00:54:47,079 --> 00:54:48,000
Piece of cake.

792
00:54:48,119 --> 00:54:49,440
So arrogant!

793
00:54:49,599 --> 00:54:51,480
Tie her tightly so she can never escape.

794
00:54:51,559 --> 00:54:52,440
Just like wrapping a dumpling.

795
00:54:52,519 --> 00:54:53,840
Be careful!

796
00:54:55,400 --> 00:54:57,079
Careful!

797
00:54:58,639 --> 00:55:01,679
You're not supposed to drop her!

798
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:04,920
Do you know how heavy she is?
Why don't you do it? It's not easy!

799
00:55:05,039 --> 00:55:06,920
I'll get you when I'm out.

800
00:55:07,000 --> 00:55:08,679
-Sorry.
-Sorry.

801
00:55:08,760 --> 00:55:09,840
It's my fault.

802
00:55:09,960 --> 00:55:11,760
-I will close it
-Close the chest.

803
00:55:12,519 --> 00:55:13,719
Lock it up.

804
00:55:14,159 --> 00:55:15,440
For real?

805
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:18,039
Count to ten, and I'll be out.

806
00:55:18,320 --> 00:55:20,599
-So arrogant.
-Come on.

807
00:55:23,199 --> 00:55:24,679
Lock up the chest.

808
00:55:28,719 --> 00:55:30,679
I have the key.
She can never escape.

809
00:55:31,559 --> 00:55:35,000
Are you okay, Fatso? Fatso!

810
00:55:35,079 --> 00:55:37,679
There's not a sound in there.
Will she die in the chest?

811
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:39,039
So strange.

812
00:55:39,119 --> 00:55:40,000
Fatso!

813
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:42,239
Will she die in the chest?

814
00:55:42,400 --> 00:55:47,960
Ten, nine, eight, seven, six,

815
00:55:48,079 --> 00:55:52,840
five, four, three, two, one!

816
00:55:53,840 --> 00:55:57,840
Fatso! Fatso! Fatso!

817
00:56:01,840 --> 00:56:04,239
Aren't you inside the chest?
I'm holding the key.

818
00:56:05,079 --> 00:56:06,760
How did you escape?

819
00:56:06,960 --> 00:56:08,559
It's magic!

820
00:56:09,480 --> 00:56:11,280
Look inside the chest.

821
00:56:15,079 --> 00:56:16,679
Is she really that good?

822
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:19,039
It's true!

823
00:56:19,519 --> 00:56:21,079
Amazing!

824
00:56:21,199 --> 00:56:25,039
If I learned this magic, I could stop
frying noodles and perform on stage.

825
00:56:25,159 --> 00:56:28,840
I'd perform in Las Vegas.

826
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:31,199
And it'd be at least $10,000
for each performance!

827
00:56:31,320 --> 00:56:35,880
-Jackpot! Tie me up first, okay?
-Tie me up first!

828
00:56:35,960 --> 00:56:37,400
You'll get your chance.
Tie me up first.

829
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:40,840
I'm fed up of giving in to you.

830
00:56:40,920 --> 00:56:43,280
-Give in already!
-Don't be such a bully!

831
00:56:44,440 --> 00:56:48,639
Buddy, you cannot imagine
how tight Master has tied me.

832
00:56:48,760 --> 00:56:52,039
I'll give a better performance than you.

833
00:56:52,320 --> 00:56:54,719
Nonsense!

834
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:56,840
Master has tied me much tighter,

835
00:56:56,960 --> 00:56:59,800
so I can perform better than you.

836
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:01,440
Just wait and see.

837
00:57:01,559 --> 00:57:04,559
Bring it on!

838
00:57:04,760 --> 00:57:06,960
Master! Master!

839
00:57:07,079 --> 00:57:08,360
Teach us the Great Escape trick, quick!

840
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:09,679
Relax.

841
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:13,320
I'll teach you something better
than the David Footballfield's stunt.

842
00:57:13,400 --> 00:57:14,960
It's a new magic trick!

843
00:57:15,039 --> 00:57:16,360
More tricks!

844
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:21,920
Tighter?

845
00:57:22,000 --> 00:57:23,440
Tighter, Master!

846
00:57:23,559 --> 00:57:24,800
Tighter?

847
00:57:25,159 --> 00:57:26,400
A bit more!

848
00:57:27,079 --> 00:57:28,239
Okay.

849
00:57:30,519 --> 00:57:31,840
Did you see that?

850
00:57:32,239 --> 00:57:33,920
I want mine to be
tighter than his, Master.

851
00:57:34,000 --> 00:57:35,360
I want to perform better.

852
00:57:37,679 --> 00:57:40,159
Let's see. Tighter, Master!

853
00:57:40,760 --> 00:57:43,719
A bit more. A bit more...

854
00:57:54,840 --> 00:57:56,559
Why are you holding knives?

855
00:57:56,960 --> 00:57:58,800
It's part of the magic trick.

856
00:57:59,679 --> 00:58:01,039
Are you going to kill us?

857
00:58:01,639 --> 00:58:03,000
Be careful with it.

858
00:58:03,159 --> 00:58:04,400
It's dangerous.

859
00:58:04,639 --> 00:58:07,639
All magic stunts are dangerous. Scared?

860
00:58:08,960 --> 00:58:10,000
Then forget about learning the trick.

861
00:58:10,280 --> 00:58:11,480
I want to learn.

862
00:58:48,880 --> 00:58:52,559
Aunt, I've found
the two substitute ghosts for you.

863
00:58:53,679 --> 00:58:55,199
Can you let me go?

864
00:59:12,639 --> 00:59:16,440
ONE YEAR LATER

865
00:59:33,920 --> 00:59:35,559
Take your sweet time.

866
00:59:39,360 --> 00:59:40,880
Want me to come hold your hands?

867
00:59:59,039 --> 01:00:00,599
Check your equipment
and report to the Master Sergeant!

868
01:00:03,360 --> 01:00:05,480
Who's not taking the shortcut?

869
01:00:05,599 --> 01:00:06,519
Ridiculous!

870
01:00:06,639 --> 01:00:09,480
If we get caught,
we'll be in deep trouble.

871
01:00:09,599 --> 01:00:11,760
Have you heard
of Code of Conduct Number 7?

872
01:00:11,880 --> 01:00:12,719
What?

873
01:00:15,239 --> 01:00:16,920
You're still at Rule 7?
The latest is Rule 8!

874
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:19,159
-What?
-You are not a soldier if you don't cheat!

875
01:00:19,239 --> 01:00:21,760
Gentlemen!
Say that one more time!

876
01:00:26,119 --> 01:00:27,760
-Yes, Master Sergeant!
-Go!

877
01:00:59,519 --> 01:01:04,719
THERE IS A PRICE TO PAY
FOR EVERY SHORTCUT YOU TAKE.

878
01:01:07,599 --> 01:01:12,199
GHOST IN THE HOUSE

879
01:01:16,800 --> 01:01:20,440
Mother, it's been a year,
and still no lottery blessing from you,

880
01:01:20,559 --> 01:01:22,639
no starter prize, no consolation prize.

881
01:01:22,760 --> 01:01:25,440
Nothing at all, not even a lucky draw.

882
01:01:25,559 --> 01:01:28,000
Please remember
to let them win some lottery.

883
01:01:28,280 --> 01:01:29,159
Thank you.

884
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:34,079
Mother, you're staying with us.
I pray to you every day.

885
01:01:34,199 --> 01:01:37,880
You must remember
to give us some lucky "4D" numbers,

886
01:01:38,000 --> 01:01:41,320
not give your granddaughters
all "D's" in exams.

887
01:01:41,400 --> 01:01:42,639
Bless us, Mother.

888
01:01:42,719 --> 01:01:44,440
Come pray to Grandma.

889
01:01:48,840 --> 01:01:50,800
Mother, you must remember,

890
01:01:50,920 --> 01:01:53,719
"4D" numbers and getting
four "D's" in exams are different.

891
01:01:53,840 --> 01:01:56,280
Don't mess up again.
Bless us!

892
01:02:02,840 --> 01:02:06,599
Mother, Lehman Brothers in America
is such a big company.

893
01:02:06,679 --> 01:02:09,840
As a deity up there,
you must've known it would go under.

894
01:02:09,960 --> 01:02:12,400
If you knew,
why didn't you inform me in advance?

895
01:02:12,519 --> 01:02:15,079
My friend's father
tipped him off in his dream.

896
01:02:15,159 --> 01:02:16,159
He managed to avoid heavy losses.

897
01:02:16,280 --> 01:02:18,280
But I didn't.
I suffered a huge losses.

898
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:19,480
You must bless me.

899
01:02:19,920 --> 01:02:22,400
Mother, are you still mad at us?

900
01:02:22,480 --> 01:02:23,920
Please don't be angry.

901
01:02:24,039 --> 01:02:27,800
We've apologized
and paid for all your medical bills.

902
01:02:27,920 --> 01:02:29,079
Look at Stella.
She's so obedient now.

903
01:02:29,159 --> 01:02:30,400
Stella, pray to Grandma.

904
01:02:30,679 --> 01:02:32,840
Mother, please bless us all.

905
01:02:43,239 --> 01:02:47,079
Mother, thank you for blessing us.
I'm finally pregnant.

906
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:53,639
Mother, you blessed me with a child,
but did not bless me with any earnings.

907
01:02:53,840 --> 01:02:56,559
How will I feed my child?

908
01:02:56,679 --> 01:02:59,599
Our business is getting worse every day.

909
01:02:59,719 --> 01:03:03,599
Please open your eyes and look after us.

910
01:03:03,679 --> 01:03:05,239
Please give us your blessing.

911
01:03:11,119 --> 01:03:12,760
Take a break.

912
01:03:12,840 --> 01:03:14,440
-Have a drink.
-Thank you.

913
01:03:15,920 --> 01:03:18,599
Our business is getting worse.
What shall we do?

914
01:03:18,679 --> 01:03:20,239
The market is so bad.

915
01:03:20,559 --> 01:03:21,599
What can we do, right?

916
01:03:22,360 --> 01:03:24,360
Amid the economic downturn,

917
01:03:24,440 --> 01:03:28,880
the government has launched a new scheme
to help small and medium businesses.

918
01:03:29,280 --> 01:03:31,400
Let's apply for it.

919
01:03:31,480 --> 01:03:32,880
Lots of incentives up for grabs.

920
01:03:33,280 --> 01:03:35,559
Don't be naive, Second Brother.

921
01:03:37,199 --> 01:03:39,719
Normally, you can apply,

922
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:41,840
but it doesn't mean you'll get approval.

923
01:03:41,960 --> 01:03:44,039
"Apply" and "approve"
are two different words.

924
01:03:44,400 --> 01:03:47,360
Many conditions apply.

925
01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:49,239
It's never easy getting money
from the government,

926
01:03:49,360 --> 01:03:51,199
but it's so much easier
in the private sector.

927
01:03:51,280 --> 01:03:52,800
Private sector? How?

928
01:03:53,239 --> 01:03:55,840
I have a friend who's a Datuk.

929
01:03:55,960 --> 01:03:57,159
Datuk?

930
01:03:57,239 --> 01:03:59,480
-Where?
-Kuala Lumpur.

931
01:03:59,920 --> 01:04:01,239
He's loaded.

932
01:04:01,320 --> 01:04:04,599
If he invests in our business,
we'll be rich.

933
01:04:04,800 --> 01:04:05,639
Are you sure?

934
01:04:05,719 --> 01:04:06,559
Okay!

935
01:04:06,679 --> 01:04:08,800
You have to be careful.
There are cheats everywhere.

936
01:04:08,960 --> 01:04:12,840
Rest assured, Big Brother, he wants
to see me. Here's my suggestion.

937
01:04:12,960 --> 01:04:16,239
Next week, why don't we, as directors
of our company, meet him in Kuala Lumpur?

938
01:04:16,320 --> 01:04:18,880
-Okay, we'll go where the riches are.
-Lovely!

939
01:04:21,119 --> 01:04:24,039
Mother, this is our last chance.

940
01:04:25,320 --> 01:04:28,960
You've been up there for a year.
You should have friends.

941
01:04:29,159 --> 01:04:31,159
Please get them to bless us too.

942
01:04:31,280 --> 01:04:34,800
Otherwise, your sons' future is doomed.

943
01:04:35,400 --> 01:04:36,920
Please give us your blessing.

944
01:04:37,239 --> 01:04:38,599
Win big!

945
01:04:39,239 --> 01:04:40,480
Bless us.

946
01:04:43,559 --> 01:04:48,199
Since Mother died,
we've not had dinner together.

947
01:04:48,559 --> 01:04:51,880
Too bad.
We're all busy with our business.

948
01:04:51,960 --> 01:04:54,920
Luckily, we made some profits initially.
Not anymore.

949
01:04:55,039 --> 01:04:57,880
Too bad. No blessing from Mother.
What can we do, right?

950
01:04:58,559 --> 01:05:00,800
Sometimes, I miss Mother.

951
01:05:01,480 --> 01:05:04,159
Enough talk. Let's eat.

952
01:05:10,280 --> 01:05:14,119
Who put a chair over there?
What is it for? Mother is no longer here.

953
01:05:14,239 --> 01:05:15,119
I didn't do it.

954
01:05:16,280 --> 01:05:18,559
Did you girls put the chair here?

955
01:05:26,400 --> 01:05:28,599
Stella, mind your words
on the Seventh Month.

956
01:05:28,679 --> 01:05:29,800
Sorry!

957
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:31,119
Take the chair away, hubby.

958
01:05:31,440 --> 01:05:32,519
I'll do it.

959
01:05:32,960 --> 01:05:34,559
She's our mother, nothing to be afraid of.

960
01:05:34,639 --> 01:05:35,880
Don't be afraid.

961
01:05:36,559 --> 01:05:37,400
Come sit closer.

962
01:05:37,519 --> 01:05:38,920
More room for us.

963
01:05:43,840 --> 01:05:45,639
This pig's trotter tastes great!

964
01:05:45,760 --> 01:05:47,840
Sister-in-law, you've finally mastered
Mother's cooking.

965
01:05:47,960 --> 01:05:50,239
This tastes exactly like Mother's cooking!

966
01:05:50,360 --> 01:05:53,519
Congratulation! It's delicious. Eat more.

967
01:05:53,719 --> 01:05:55,760
I didn't cook that dish.
Didn't you bring it here?

968
01:05:56,960 --> 01:05:59,079
Don't look at me. It wasn't me.

969
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:02,320
I didn't bring it either.

970
01:06:03,079 --> 01:06:04,199
I bought it.

971
01:06:04,920 --> 01:06:06,960
You almost scared us to death.

972
01:06:07,079 --> 01:06:09,719
Dear, I bought it
from the coffee shop near our place.

973
01:06:09,840 --> 01:06:12,559
It tastes exactly like Mother's cooking.

974
01:06:13,159 --> 01:06:14,800
Why didn't you mention it before?

975
01:06:15,039 --> 01:06:17,199
Come on, let's eat.

976
01:06:29,840 --> 01:06:31,280
Why is there another chair?

977
01:06:37,519 --> 01:06:39,920
No, the chair was here all along.

978
01:06:40,000 --> 01:06:41,920
The chair was never here.
Ask you wife.

979
01:06:43,880 --> 01:06:45,239
He's right.

980
01:06:45,320 --> 01:06:46,199
See?

981
01:06:48,320 --> 01:06:50,480
Big Brother, that chair is gone!

982
01:06:50,920 --> 01:06:52,440
I remember placing the chair over there.

983
01:06:52,519 --> 01:06:53,800
Why is it here?

984
01:06:54,519 --> 01:06:55,679
Is it grandma?

985
01:06:55,800 --> 01:06:57,199
She wants to join us for dinner.

986
01:07:00,360 --> 01:07:02,079
Mind your words. Just eat!

987
01:07:03,440 --> 01:07:07,880
Tell me, did anyone talk nonsense
at the altar earlier?

988
01:07:08,320 --> 01:07:11,320
-No!
-Someone must have done it!

989
01:07:53,280 --> 01:07:55,639
Mother! Mother!

990
01:07:57,079 --> 01:08:02,119
Ong, have you seen my bra?

991
01:08:09,719 --> 01:08:11,519
Damn!

992
01:08:11,920 --> 01:08:13,719
I saw Mother!

993
01:08:16,079 --> 01:08:20,720
Darling! Darling!

994
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:24,680
What's up, dear?

995
01:08:25,359 --> 01:08:26,600
I saw Mother!

996
01:08:27,239 --> 01:08:28,159
Mother?

997
01:08:28,760 --> 01:08:29,680
Where?

998
01:08:29,800 --> 01:08:33,000
Here, she was here,
asking me for her bra.

999
01:08:33,119 --> 01:08:35,159
I'm not kidding!

1000
01:08:35,600 --> 01:08:37,600
Were you dreaming?

1001
01:08:37,720 --> 01:08:38,880
Impossible!

1002
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:41,840
It's true. She was sitting over here,
right at this spot.

1003
01:08:42,399 --> 01:08:43,960
I'm not lying!

1004
01:08:47,319 --> 01:08:52,840
Ong, have you seen my bra?

1005
01:08:52,960 --> 01:08:57,000
The red one with Mickey Mouse prints.

1006
01:08:57,520 --> 01:09:01,279
I'll buy you another one.

1007
01:09:01,840 --> 01:09:05,159
Get it in Singapore.

1008
01:09:31,319 --> 01:09:33,960
Boss, you're selling green tea too?

1009
01:09:34,079 --> 01:09:37,640
Yes. The trend follows
the dead to the underworld.

1010
01:09:37,760 --> 01:09:40,560
They'll still prefer
their favorite drinks down there.

1011
01:09:40,760 --> 01:09:42,640
-"Down there"?
-Of course!

1012
01:09:43,039 --> 01:09:44,039
How can I help you?

1013
01:09:46,479 --> 01:09:47,479
Do you sell bras?

1014
01:09:48,880 --> 01:09:51,119
Bras? You came here to buy a bra?

1015
01:09:53,640 --> 01:09:54,920
Are you serious?

1016
01:09:55,439 --> 01:09:56,479
I've no choice.

1017
01:09:56,600 --> 01:09:59,600
My mother haunts me every day,
asking me for her bra.

1018
01:10:01,319 --> 01:10:04,199
You're the first customer
to make such a request.

1019
01:10:04,279 --> 01:10:07,960
-Do you have?
-Okay, I'll have them tailor-made for you.

1020
01:10:08,079 --> 01:10:09,760
Good. Give me two pairs.

1021
01:10:09,880 --> 01:10:12,079
-Color?
-Black and red.

1022
01:10:13,119 --> 01:10:14,039
I'll take it down.

1023
01:10:14,680 --> 01:10:16,319
Can you add Mickey Mouse stickers to them?

1024
01:10:17,800 --> 01:10:18,880
Mickey Mouse?

1025
01:10:19,840 --> 01:10:22,439
-Your mother likes Mickey Mouse?
-There's nothing I can do!

1026
01:10:22,560 --> 01:10:24,840
She keeps demanding
Mickey Mouse on her bra.

1027
01:10:24,960 --> 01:10:27,119
If you can do it,
I can burn it for her.

1028
01:10:28,680 --> 01:10:31,800
Burn Mickey Mouse?
Can't do it. Copyright infringement.

1029
01:10:32,680 --> 01:10:36,199
You're right. This is such a pain!
I have a suggestion.

1030
01:10:36,560 --> 01:10:41,319
Can you make it so that
the Chinese know it's Mickey Mouse,

1031
01:10:41,520 --> 01:10:44,199
but Westerners can't tell.

1032
01:10:52,840 --> 01:10:54,199
You're so hilarious!

1033
01:10:56,399 --> 01:10:58,800
I'll try my best.

1034
01:10:58,920 --> 01:11:01,640
-It's settled. I'll collect them tomorrow.
-Okay, okay.

1035
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:04,039
What's her cup size?

1036
01:11:07,439 --> 01:11:10,520
She's been gone for a year,
but has never told me.

1037
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:11,560
What shall I do?

1038
01:11:12,279 --> 01:11:14,319
We play safe, give her a large cup size.

1039
01:11:14,560 --> 01:11:19,720
Large? Large one?
Yes, the larger, the better.

1040
01:11:20,119 --> 01:11:22,000
Okay. Okay.

1041
01:11:44,159 --> 01:11:48,560
Hui, have you eaten?

1042
01:11:48,760 --> 01:11:49,840
Yes.

1043
01:11:54,720 --> 01:11:55,600
Darling!

1044
01:11:56,279 --> 01:11:57,159
Darling!

1045
01:11:57,800 --> 01:11:59,800
Did you ask me if I've eaten?

1046
01:12:00,039 --> 01:12:00,880
Darling!

1047
01:12:05,520 --> 01:12:06,920
You're insane.

1048
01:12:07,039 --> 01:12:08,920
You've been asking me
the same question for days.

1049
01:12:09,119 --> 01:12:12,399
And will you please
get the television repaired?

1050
01:12:12,479 --> 01:12:14,479
It's been broken for days.
I think the wires are loose.

1051
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:16,720
I've missed my favorite drama series.

1052
01:12:16,840 --> 01:12:17,760
So annoying.

1053
01:12:19,239 --> 01:12:21,680
Look at this television.

1054
01:12:24,319 --> 01:12:25,600
Must be a loose wire.

1055
01:12:34,920 --> 01:12:37,800
Mother! She's inside the TV!

1056
01:12:39,399 --> 01:12:42,000
No! Where is she?
You're insane!

1057
01:12:54,520 --> 01:12:55,760
Loose wire...

1058
01:13:01,960 --> 01:13:05,359
Mother is in the television!
She's inside!

1059
01:13:07,199 --> 01:13:08,960
Don't scare me!

1060
01:13:11,279 --> 01:13:15,359
You! It's not the television.
You're the one with a loose wire!

1061
01:13:15,800 --> 01:13:17,840
You do the adjustment.
I'll watch from here.

1062
01:13:27,239 --> 01:13:30,399
Look. Look carefully.

1063
01:13:34,039 --> 01:13:35,039
See anything?

1064
01:13:36,520 --> 01:13:38,520
This is a nice show.

1065
01:13:39,239 --> 01:13:41,680
What a bad daughter-in-law!

1066
01:13:50,319 --> 01:13:51,680
I dreamed of Mother!

1067
01:13:54,880 --> 01:13:59,560
Hui, have you eaten?

1068
01:13:59,680 --> 01:14:03,159
What a bad daughter-in-law!

1069
01:14:09,960 --> 01:14:13,239
I can't take it anymore.

1070
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:18,520
Mother sits on my bed every night,
asking for her Mickey Mouse bra.

1071
01:14:18,960 --> 01:14:20,640
I can't stand it anymore.

1072
01:14:21,319 --> 01:14:24,960
I bought her a large Mickey Mouse bra,

1073
01:14:25,079 --> 01:14:27,680
but she's still not happy
and continues to haunt me.

1074
01:14:27,760 --> 01:14:29,000
It's worse for me.

1075
01:14:29,279 --> 01:14:30,239
How?

1076
01:14:30,399 --> 01:14:33,399
She only haunts you at night,
but she haunts me all day.

1077
01:14:33,520 --> 01:14:38,760
-That's bad.
-I hear her words every minute,

1078
01:14:39,000 --> 01:14:41,039
but see nobody around me.

1079
01:14:42,079 --> 01:14:44,159
Now, she has a new trick.

1080
01:14:44,399 --> 01:14:45,319
What is it?

1081
01:14:45,439 --> 01:14:48,159
She hides in the television
and scares me.

1082
01:14:48,600 --> 01:14:49,640
Which channel?

1083
01:14:49,760 --> 01:14:50,920
Every channel.

1084
01:14:51,359 --> 01:14:56,000
She kept repeating the same words
until my head almost cracked.

1085
01:14:57,319 --> 01:14:59,319
Second Brother, you look very relaxed.

1086
01:14:59,439 --> 01:15:00,760
Mother didn't harass you?

1087
01:15:00,840 --> 01:15:01,880
Nope.

1088
01:15:02,000 --> 01:15:03,000
Impossible!

1089
01:15:03,079 --> 01:15:04,319
Maybe she thinks I'm a good son.

1090
01:15:06,199 --> 01:15:08,239
You must be joking.

1091
01:15:08,319 --> 01:15:09,640
I'll tell you honestly,

1092
01:15:09,760 --> 01:15:13,079
if not for that packet of blood you took,
Mother would still be alive.

1093
01:15:13,199 --> 01:15:15,119
-You're wrong.
-Why?

1094
01:15:15,199 --> 01:15:17,960
Mother willingly volunteered
to save Stella.

1095
01:15:18,039 --> 01:15:21,239
In danger, who would you save?
Mother or daughter?

1096
01:15:21,319 --> 01:15:25,199
I asked for your opinions,
but both of you just avoided the question!

1097
01:15:25,319 --> 01:15:29,119
She's our only Mother, the one and only.

1098
01:15:29,239 --> 01:15:32,720
Even if she pulled the oxygen tube,
I would've plugged it back.

1099
01:15:32,800 --> 01:15:34,239
Now you're saying this!

1100
01:15:34,399 --> 01:15:37,560
Isn't it too late?
Your daughter isn't born yet--

1101
01:15:37,640 --> 01:15:40,479
Don't you mention my daughter.

1102
01:15:40,600 --> 01:15:42,159
You did it too.

1103
01:15:42,239 --> 01:15:43,239
Stop fighting.

1104
01:15:43,640 --> 01:15:45,359
It's been over a year, for goodness sake.

1105
01:15:46,600 --> 01:15:49,479
But I don't understand,
why didn't Mother look for you?

1106
01:15:50,079 --> 01:15:52,039
Big Brother,
how could you say such things?

1107
01:15:52,159 --> 01:15:55,640
Mother must have tried haunting him,
but in vain.

1108
01:15:56,039 --> 01:15:58,840
You've moved twice in a year,
hiding from Mother?

1109
01:15:58,920 --> 01:16:01,319
-Nonsense!
-There's no use hiding.

1110
01:16:01,399 --> 01:16:02,920
She'll find you one day.

1111
01:16:03,000 --> 01:16:04,119
I'm not afraid of her!

1112
01:16:04,199 --> 01:16:08,600
Why should I be?
She may even help me win the lottery!

1113
01:16:08,840 --> 01:16:10,720
Don't be so mean to your own brother!

1114
01:16:14,199 --> 01:16:15,399
I'm not afraid!

1115
01:17:31,000 --> 01:17:32,079
You gave me a fright!

1116
01:17:32,159 --> 01:17:34,439
Don't pat on my shoulder from behind.
It's the Seventh Month!

1117
01:17:34,520 --> 01:17:35,840
You're so cowardly!

1118
01:17:36,880 --> 01:17:39,840
Let me tell you something.
They've seen Mother around.

1119
01:17:40,039 --> 01:17:41,920
I think we're next!

1120
01:17:45,359 --> 01:17:46,399
Let's go.

1121
01:17:46,840 --> 01:17:47,960
Are you sure?

1122
01:19:07,039 --> 01:19:09,199
Hubby! Hubby!

1123
01:19:09,600 --> 01:19:11,039
Give me a tissue.

1124
01:19:12,039 --> 01:19:15,079
Hurry. My eyes are hurting.

1125
01:19:18,199 --> 01:19:20,039
Hurry up!

1126
01:19:27,960 --> 01:19:29,159
Your tissue.

1127
01:19:31,680 --> 01:19:33,199
You gave it to me, right?

1128
01:19:33,319 --> 01:19:35,000
No, I just got here.

1129
01:19:35,279 --> 01:19:36,199
Then what's in my hand?

1130
01:19:36,319 --> 01:19:37,680
But I just entered the room.

1131
01:19:37,960 --> 01:19:39,359
Trying to scare me?

1132
01:19:39,479 --> 01:19:42,479
I've wet my pants,
I'm so scared. Childish!

1133
01:19:42,760 --> 01:19:44,479
Says who?
I'm not that easy-going.

1134
01:20:27,479 --> 01:20:31,640
Darling, tell me honestly,
did you help me wash my face earlier?

1135
01:20:31,760 --> 01:20:32,600
No.

1136
01:20:33,479 --> 01:20:34,439
Come on.

1137
01:20:34,680 --> 01:20:35,760
No.

1138
01:20:35,960 --> 01:20:38,640
-Don't lie to me, please.
-No!

1139
01:20:39,319 --> 01:20:42,600
-Can you lie to me? Say yes.
-What's wrong with you?

1140
01:20:42,720 --> 01:20:45,039
I'll feel better this way.

1141
01:20:45,319 --> 01:20:47,600
You're becoming more cowardly
as you grow older.

1142
01:20:48,640 --> 01:20:52,640
I'm getting the feeling
that Mother is already in here.

1143
01:20:53,039 --> 01:20:56,119
Why are you so afraid?
She lived with us before.

1144
01:20:56,239 --> 01:20:57,880
Don't worry. Just sleep.

1145
01:21:00,079 --> 01:21:02,680
We'll burn some incense for her tomorrow.

1146
01:21:02,760 --> 01:21:03,800
Okay.

1147
01:21:05,159 --> 01:21:07,600
Kiong...

1148
01:21:09,399 --> 01:21:11,720
Did you hear Mother calling me?

1149
01:21:11,840 --> 01:21:13,399
No!

1150
01:21:16,319 --> 01:21:18,479
Kiong...

1151
01:21:19,960 --> 01:21:21,920
This time, I did!

1152
01:21:22,000 --> 01:21:25,039
Don't scare us, Mother.
I admit I'm not a good son.

1153
01:21:25,119 --> 01:21:27,840
I'll burn some incense
for you tomorrow. Please!

1154
01:21:28,039 --> 01:21:30,279
-Don't scare us!
-Let's sleep.

1155
01:21:32,079 --> 01:21:33,319
Kiong...

1156
01:21:34,239 --> 01:21:39,479
Don't trouble yourself over where I sleep.

1157
01:21:39,600 --> 01:21:42,560
I can sleep anywhere.

1158
01:21:47,359 --> 01:21:48,600
You saw Mother too?

1159
01:21:48,680 --> 01:21:50,600
That was your wish, wasn't it?

1160
01:21:50,680 --> 01:21:52,319
Now that it's has come true,
aren't you two delighted?

1161
01:21:52,399 --> 01:21:55,760
-What are you talking about?
-Why would we want it to happen?

1162
01:21:55,840 --> 01:21:57,239
Stop playing dumb!

1163
01:21:57,399 --> 01:22:01,760
Both of you were here last night,
jealous of Mother not haunting me,

1164
01:22:01,840 --> 01:22:05,039
so you cursed me, and now she did
come haunt me. Are you two satisfied?

1165
01:22:05,159 --> 01:22:08,159
-But we went to Johor yesterday.
-Exactly.

1166
01:22:08,239 --> 01:22:09,640
Stop denying it!

1167
01:22:09,760 --> 01:22:11,760
If you don't believe me,
I'll show you my passport.

1168
01:22:11,840 --> 01:22:13,520
Yes, we were in Johor.

1169
01:22:13,880 --> 01:22:15,199
Stop denying it!

1170
01:22:15,439 --> 01:22:17,520
I'm not a fool!

1171
01:22:19,119 --> 01:22:20,920
Are you dreaming, Second Brother?

1172
01:22:22,600 --> 01:22:23,600
Dreaming?

1173
01:22:24,039 --> 01:22:26,000
But I remember we meeting here!

1174
01:22:26,439 --> 01:22:29,039
You're saying
even our meeting here was a dream?

1175
01:22:31,239 --> 01:22:34,159
And I continued to dream of Mother.

1176
01:22:34,600 --> 01:22:36,359
She almost scared me to death.

1177
01:22:38,119 --> 01:22:40,640
-I also dreamed of Mother.
-Me too.

1178
01:22:41,680 --> 01:22:43,079
Both of you?

1179
01:22:44,760 --> 01:22:46,399
Mother appeared in all our dreams.

1180
01:22:46,880 --> 01:22:48,119
What's her motive?

1181
01:22:48,199 --> 01:22:49,039
Right.

1182
01:22:50,880 --> 01:22:54,479
Big Brother,
did you perform the prayers correctly?

1183
01:22:54,560 --> 01:22:55,760
Do you know the proper procedures?

1184
01:22:56,399 --> 01:22:58,239
What are you trying to say?

1185
01:22:58,880 --> 01:23:02,039
I don't need you juniors to teach me.

1186
01:23:02,680 --> 01:23:05,880
In fact, I should've told you earlier,

1187
01:23:06,279 --> 01:23:07,680
I'm not Mother's only son.

1188
01:23:07,800 --> 01:23:11,039
Each of us should take turns monthly
to offer her prayers.

1189
01:23:11,720 --> 01:23:12,720
I can't do it.

1190
01:23:12,840 --> 01:23:15,840
Her tablet doesn't suit
the avant-garde design of my house.

1191
01:23:16,039 --> 01:23:18,399
Same here.
You know that I'm busy.

1192
01:23:18,479 --> 01:23:21,960
"Can't"? "Busy"?
I don't care! We take turns praying.

1193
01:23:26,159 --> 01:23:27,560
Isn't that your friend?

1194
01:23:29,039 --> 01:23:31,359
Wow, looks like he's having a good time.

1195
01:23:34,319 --> 01:23:36,880
-Hey, buddy!
-Both of you, wait for me over there.

1196
01:23:37,640 --> 01:23:39,840
Lucky you, driving a Mercedes!

1197
01:23:39,920 --> 01:23:43,800
Mine broke down.
This is my maid's errand car.

1198
01:23:43,880 --> 01:23:45,800
You must be earning a lot.
What's you job?

1199
01:23:45,920 --> 01:23:47,960
I don't need to work.

1200
01:23:48,079 --> 01:23:51,319
My mother's blessing me
with such good fortune.

1201
01:23:51,399 --> 01:23:54,399
I keep asking her not to let me
win the lottery again, but in vain.

1202
01:23:54,520 --> 01:23:58,079
I even won first prize
with unlucky numbers like 4444.

1203
01:23:58,159 --> 01:24:00,760
I just keep winning.

1204
01:24:00,840 --> 01:24:04,640
Even the bookies shun me.

1205
01:24:04,960 --> 01:24:06,680
Your mother is that powerful?

1206
01:24:06,800 --> 01:24:11,279
Didn't you know? When an elder dies,
the timing is important.

1207
01:24:11,359 --> 01:24:13,159
If she dies at midnight,

1208
01:24:13,239 --> 01:24:16,239
she takes away all fortune
and leaves nothing for the descendants.

1209
01:24:16,319 --> 01:24:19,720
But if the time is in the morning
such as 7:00 a.m.,

1210
01:24:19,840 --> 01:24:22,520
the descendants will prosper,
leaving nothing for the deceased.

1211
01:24:22,600 --> 01:24:26,600
And if she dies at noon,
both parties will split the luck.

1212
01:24:26,720 --> 01:24:29,079
Get it? I doubt you do!

1213
01:24:29,640 --> 01:24:30,920
So your mother died in the morning?

1214
01:24:31,000 --> 01:24:32,960
It was supposed to be at midnight.

1215
01:24:33,680 --> 01:24:37,039
The doctor tried to revive her
with injections and a defibrillator,

1216
01:24:37,159 --> 01:24:40,119
and shook her through the night.

1217
01:24:40,199 --> 01:24:45,079
She struggled all the way until daybreak,

1218
01:24:45,159 --> 01:24:47,560
thereby blessing us with good fortune.

1219
01:24:47,720 --> 01:24:49,760
That's what I call a great mother.

1220
01:24:50,960 --> 01:24:52,159
I need to go.

1221
01:24:52,600 --> 01:24:54,880
Forty thousand.

1222
01:24:57,000 --> 01:24:58,359
Let's go have some fun!

1223
01:24:58,960 --> 01:25:00,560
You'll be fined for illegal parking!

1224
01:25:01,159 --> 01:25:03,680
What's the big deal?

1225
01:25:03,800 --> 01:25:05,319
I'm loaded!

1226
01:25:08,439 --> 01:25:09,920
Jealous of me?

1227
01:25:13,880 --> 01:25:15,720
This is the life!

1228
01:25:18,199 --> 01:25:22,239
Our mother died at night.
She left us with nothing.

1229
01:25:23,319 --> 01:25:27,800
After hearing what he said,
I realize Mother cannot bless us anymore.

1230
01:25:28,000 --> 01:25:30,319
So all the prayers are a waste of time.

1231
01:25:30,399 --> 01:25:32,279
Forget it then.

1232
01:25:32,359 --> 01:25:36,680
How can you say that?
We're her sons, for goodness sake!

1233
01:25:37,079 --> 01:25:41,520
Big Brother, if you try too hard,
the situation may backfire.

1234
01:25:41,800 --> 01:25:43,600
Our luck may turn from bad to worse.

1235
01:25:44,800 --> 01:25:47,399
Now I know
why Mother appeared in our dreams.

1236
01:25:47,520 --> 01:25:48,359
Why?

1237
01:25:48,439 --> 01:25:50,479
She's trying to tell us
she can't bless us anymore.

1238
01:25:50,560 --> 01:25:53,760
So, by scaring us,
she hopes we'll stay away from her.

1239
01:25:54,079 --> 01:25:55,720
Therefore, we should stop all the prayers.

1240
01:25:56,319 --> 01:25:57,239
Sounds logical.

1241
01:25:58,800 --> 01:26:00,520
What do we do with the tablet?

1242
01:26:01,680 --> 01:26:04,479
Listen, I know someone from a temple.

1243
01:26:04,600 --> 01:26:06,119
The temple is quite remote,

1244
01:26:06,199 --> 01:26:10,520
but we can house the tablet there
at discount rates. What do you think?

1245
01:26:10,600 --> 01:26:12,479
-I'm good!
-Good?

1246
01:26:12,880 --> 01:26:13,960
How about you, Big Brother?

1247
01:26:14,079 --> 01:26:17,079
When Mother was alive,
you sent her to an old folks home.

1248
01:26:17,159 --> 01:26:19,880
Now that she's dead,
you're sending her to an old temple?

1249
01:26:19,960 --> 01:26:21,960
Have you no humanity?

1250
01:26:22,079 --> 01:26:24,439
There's nothing we can do.

1251
01:26:24,560 --> 01:26:27,840
There's no point continuing the prayers.
My mind is made up.

1252
01:26:27,960 --> 01:26:29,159
Me too.

1253
01:26:29,239 --> 01:26:30,399
What about you?

1254
01:26:30,479 --> 01:26:33,359
Big Brother, if you insist,
do it at your own risk.

1255
01:26:33,439 --> 01:26:36,720
-Don't say we didn't warn you.
-Think about it.

1256
01:26:39,359 --> 01:26:41,119
Who will bring Mother to the temple?

1257
01:27:25,119 --> 01:27:28,600
Mother, don't get the wrong idea.

1258
01:27:28,680 --> 01:27:31,399
We're not bad sons.

1259
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:35,840
We've found a nice place for you.

1260
01:27:35,960 --> 01:27:37,319
It's divine.

1261
01:27:37,960 --> 01:27:43,239
See? Beautiful scenery on your left,

1262
01:27:44,319 --> 01:27:47,000
and your old buddies on your right.

1263
01:27:47,239 --> 01:27:49,720
They're all staying here with you.

1264
01:27:50,520 --> 01:27:53,439
They'll keep you happy.

1265
01:27:54,039 --> 01:27:56,600
You can chat with them,

1266
01:27:56,840 --> 01:27:59,239
play games, talk about the old days...

1267
01:27:59,319 --> 01:28:04,560
The air is very fresh.

1268
01:28:05,399 --> 01:28:08,800
Butterflies, birds...

1269
01:28:09,039 --> 01:28:11,039
Look! And even parrots!

1270
01:28:14,800 --> 01:28:15,920
Mind your step.

1271
01:28:16,039 --> 01:28:19,079
Be careful. Slowly.

1272
01:28:19,960 --> 01:28:21,760
Up the stairs.

1273
01:28:28,760 --> 01:28:31,560
Mother, here's your mansion.

1274
01:29:16,479 --> 01:29:18,119
Hello?

1275
01:29:18,600 --> 01:29:20,399
I'll tell you something very frightening.

1276
01:29:20,479 --> 01:29:21,800
Come here quickly.

1277
01:29:22,239 --> 01:29:23,279
Hurry!

1278
01:29:37,039 --> 01:29:40,960
Big Brother, why didn't you bring
Mother's tablet into the temple?

1279
01:29:41,039 --> 01:29:42,239
-I did.
-Then?

1280
01:29:42,319 --> 01:29:44,359
I sent her in,
but she flew back here.

1281
01:29:45,600 --> 01:29:46,680
Flew back here?

1282
01:29:46,760 --> 01:29:48,520
Are you sure you weren't daydreaming?

1283
01:29:48,600 --> 01:29:52,640
Or was it that you made a mistake?

1284
01:29:53,279 --> 01:29:55,399
Why won't the two of you believe me?

1285
01:29:55,479 --> 01:29:58,399
I brought Mother in personally,

1286
01:29:58,479 --> 01:30:01,279
but when I came out,
she was already inside,

1287
01:30:01,399 --> 01:30:04,000
even before I opened the car door!

1288
01:30:08,640 --> 01:30:11,720
-Don't cry.
-Stop crying.

1289
01:30:12,319 --> 01:30:13,560
I'm not crying.

1290
01:30:13,960 --> 01:30:16,159
Do you know how frightened I am?

1291
01:30:17,079 --> 01:30:19,960
Listen, don't try to be funny,
Big Brother.

1292
01:30:20,039 --> 01:30:23,119
Tablets don't fly out on their own.
You must be joking, right?

1293
01:30:23,199 --> 01:30:25,880
-Is this a prank?
-Why are you both so stubborn?

1294
01:30:26,079 --> 01:30:29,920
Why won't the two of you just believe me?

1295
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:33,119
Why would I need to lie?
Why are you doubting me?

1296
01:30:33,239 --> 01:30:35,720
-Why?
-Okay, we believe you.

1297
01:30:35,840 --> 01:30:37,920
I think Mother wants us
to send her in together.

1298
01:30:38,000 --> 01:30:39,119
Here we are.

1299
01:30:40,199 --> 01:30:42,000
Here we come, Mother.

1300
01:30:42,680 --> 01:30:44,319
All right, let's send her in together.

1301
01:31:03,880 --> 01:31:06,880
He's doing all this
because he's unwilling to do it alone.

1302
